repoman (1.0.0-1) noble; urgency=low

  * 1.0 release — stable and shippable.
  * UI consistency pass: standardize "Upgrade Assistant" and "pre-upgrade" naming
    throughout menus, window titles, shortcuts popup, and help-docs.
  * Fix CompatChecker button order (Close left, Check right — was reversed).
  * Fix missing repos dialog: "Skip" -> "Cancel"; remove double suggested-action.
  * Fix "Disable All Repositories" window title (removed question mark).
  * Fix "About Repoman" menu label capitalisation.
  * Fix "Remove Multiple Repositories" window title.
  * Standardize state file terminology: "Save/Load state" throughout (was
    "configuration" / "configs" in file dialogs and filter label).
  * Remove phantom dependencies: python3-xlib and gir1.2-packagekitglib-1.0.
  * Add AppStream screenshots to metainfo.xml.
  * Help-docs: config reference updated to v2 format with correct key-bundling
    description; cross-machine restore classification flow documented.
  * Help-docs: hamburger nav dropdown synced with full mkdocs.yml nav (was
    missing Why repoman, Installation, State Management pages).
  * Help-docs: keyboard shortcuts table added to Getting Started.
  * Help-docs: companion tools section (Software Updater, Software & Updates,
    Install a .deb) added to Managing Repositories.
  * README: PPA install instructions added; PackageKit claim corrected;
    Desktop integration notes section added; Building the docs section added.
  * Remove window positioning code; placement left entirely to the window manager.

 -- Tecktron Studios <software@tecktron.net>  Tue, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

repoman (0.2.1-1) noble; urgency=low

  * Rename app ID to net.tecktron.repoman (owned domain, no github dependency).
  * Change in-app help URL to repoman.tecktron.net (stable owned subdomain).
  * Restore wizard: Existing vs Adding redesign; matched repos with current suite
    skip network checks and only sync enabled state.
  * Info popovers and tooltips on compat checker suite-agnostic and non-PPA rows.
  * Fix availability icon (tecktron-repoman-available, was pamac-tray-no-update).
  * Fix: entry_to_repository normalises .list source paths to .sources.
  * Fix: _show_missing_repos_dialog guards against empty missing list.
  * Remove window positioning code entirely. GTK4 removed gtk_window_move() and
    made sane window placement basically impossible without either fighting the
    toolkit through undocumented internals or accepting Adwaita overlay dialogs
    that look completely out of place on any non-GNOME desktop. Window placement
    is now left entirely to the window manager, which is what GTK4 intended.

